SUMMARY:PCDC Contra Dance
DESCRIPTION:Contra Dancing\nThis is a no-official-host dance to live music at the Fulton Community Center\, 68 SW Miles Street in Portland. All are welcome!\n\nMusic from **The Nettles**\, known for their high energy playing and improvisational style. Sometimes folky\, sometimes jazzy\, always spicy. Calling by **Rich Goss**. Contra dance lesson for newcomers at 7 pm\, dancing from 7:30 to 10:30 with a short break halfway through.\n\nBring water\, clothing appropriate for indoor aerobic activity and smooth-soled shoes for dancing. Please do not wear scented products to the dance.\n\nCost: $15 entry fee allows us to break even\; sliding scale is available\; cash\, check or credit card.\n\nMasking and up-to-date vaccination is recommended but not required. For more information about PCDC: www.portlandcountrydance.org. *[Note: there are always plenty of folks on the dance floor regardless of how many sign up on Meetup!]*
